<p>So what I would like to do is make a countdown based on the date from mysql and make it going down in live mode without the need to refresh.</p>  <p>Code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php      $date = strtotime($row_tournaments['date']);     $remaining = $date - time();     $days_remaining = floor($remaining / 86400);     $hours_remaining = floor(($remaining % 86400) / 3600);     $minutes_remaining = floor(($remaining % 3600) / 60);     $seconds_remaining = ($remaining % 60);     echo "&lt;p&gt;$days_remaining &lt;span style='font-size:.3em;'&gt;dias&lt;/span&gt; $hours_remaining &lt;span style='font-size:.3em;'&gt;horas&lt;/span&gt; $minutes_remaining &lt;span style='font-size:.3em;'&gt;minutos&lt;/span&gt; $seconds_remaining &lt;span style='font-size:.3em;'&gt;segundos&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"; ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This works fine but I need to refresh so I can see the time going down.</p>  <pre><code>$date = strtotime($row_tournaments['date']); </code></pre>  <p>This is geting the date from database which the format is:</p>  <pre><code>2015-10-11 08:15:31 </code></pre>